tinal luminal disorder","Upper gastrointestinal structural disorder","Pancreatic luminal disorder","Small bowel luminal disorder","Small bowel mucosal disorder"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe Zollinger Ellison syndrome is caused by a non\u2013beta islet cell, gastrin-secreting tumour, which is usually found in the pancreas. These rare neuroendocrine tumours stimulate constant maximal gastric acid secretion. As the result, the patient will present with epigastric pain (peptic ulceration) and diarrhoea (malabsorption). The syndrome can therefore be classified as an \u003Cstrong\u003Eupper gastrointestinal luminal disorder\u003C/strong\u003E. The excess acid production leads to malabsorption through several mechanisms:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInactivation of pancreatic enzymes\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDamage to the small intestinal mucosa\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPrecipitation of bile acids\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt would not be classified as an \u003Cstrong\u003Eupper gastrointestinal structural disorder\u003C/strong\u003E as there is no physical obstruction or anatomical abnormality. It is not a \u003Cstrong\u003Epancreatic luminal disorder\u003C/strong\u003E as the primary pathology is not in the pancreas (although pancreatic enzyme function is affected). It is not a \u003Cstrong\u003Esmall bowel luminal disorder\u003C/strong\u003E or \u003Cstrong\u003Esmall bowel mucosal disorder\u003C/strong\u003E as the primary defect is in acid secretion from the stomach, though these areas are affected secondarily.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Zollinger Ellison syndrome causes malabsorption through excessive gastric acid secretion, making it an upper gastrointestinal luminal disorder.","Zollinger Ellison syndrome is caused by gastrin-secreting tumours leading to gastric acid hypersecretion."],"references":["Yang RH, Chu YK. Zollinger-Ellison syndrome: Revelation of the gastrinoma triangle. Radiol Case Rep. 2015 Dec 3;10(1):827. doi: 10.2484/rcr.v10i1.827. PMID: 27408649; PMCID: PMC4921170.","Cho MS, Kasi A. Zollinger-Ellison Syndrome. 2022 Nov 21. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30726029.","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52589"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15233"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52589","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52589"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-03T15:43:50+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-03T15:44:25+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7924"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67133"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{